1
00:03:10,780 --> 00:03:12,710
Haven't you finished reading yet?

2
00:03:22,180 --> 00:03:22,980
I brought a yak

3
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:23,970
from home.

4
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,460
I'm busy.

5
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:31,520
You make lunch.

6
00:03:32,690 --> 00:03:33,430
There's no one else at the base.

7
00:03:33,430 --> 00:03:34,210
Don't make too much.

8
00:03:34,210 --> 00:03:35,270
We can't finish it.

9
00:03:36,340 --> 00:03:36,910
Okay.

10
00:03:37,460 --> 00:03:38,460
I also brought milk.

11
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:40,120
I'll heat a bowl for you later.

12
00:03:40,410 --> 00:03:41,000
Okay.

13
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:07,870
Make way! Make way!

14
00:04:07,870 --> 00:04:08,690
Make way! Make way!

15
00:04:08,690 --> 00:04:10,120
Make way! Watch out!

16
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,930
Make way! Watch out!

17
00:04:13,590 --> 00:04:14,620
Get out of the car!

18
00:04:14,690 --> 00:04:15,120
Okay.

19
00:04:25,890 --> 00:04:26,560
Tell me.

20
00:04:26,630 --> 00:04:27,630
What's wrong now?

21
00:04:28,190 --> 00:04:29,240
It can't climb slopes.

22
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:31,300
Rev it too much and it starts gasping.

23
00:04:32,330 --> 00:04:33,630
Stop flooring it here.

24
00:04:34,310 --> 00:04:36,570
You’re making a mess with all that smoke.

25
00:04:38,430 --> 00:04:39,120
Have you fallen off before?

26
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:39,810
No, no.

27
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:40,920
I ride just fine.

28
00:04:41,010 --> 00:04:43,270
You must have broken it when you fixed it.

29
00:04:44,860 --> 00:04:45,860
This kid.

30
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:47,480
Even when you go see a doctor,

31
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:48,220
you can’t guarantee

32
00:04:48,220 --> 00:04:49,860
they'll cure you in one visit.

33
00:04:49,860 --> 00:04:50,950
Am I right?

34
00:04:53,130 --> 00:04:53,920
Well, this time,

35
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:54,920
you can't charge me again.

36
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:55,800
Last time you took

37
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:56,430
50 yuan from me.

38
00:04:56,430 --> 00:04:57,690
You can't ask for more!

39
00:05:00,430 --> 00:05:01,250
Leave it here.

40
00:05:01,770 --> 00:05:02,970
Let me check it again.

41
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,490
I’m telling you,

42
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:05,330
if there are no parts that need replacing,

43
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:07,040
it’s fine if I don’t charge you.

44
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,430
I’ll come pick it up tomorrow.

45
00:05:08,430 --> 00:05:08,870
Okay.

46
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:10,210
Let's go.

47
00:05:10,510 --> 00:05:11,440
I'm leaving too.

48
00:05:12,450 --> 00:05:13,380
What do you want?

49
00:05:21,220 --> 00:05:21,920
Money.

50
00:05:22,390 --> 00:05:23,300
Money.

51
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:29,570
How did you get out?

52
00:05:30,620 --> 00:05:31,430
Is it just you?

53
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:34,300
After the Mountain Patrol left,

54
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:35,960
I followed the tire tracks

55
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:37,159
for 2 days

56
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:39,950
and hitched a ride back

57
00:05:40,130 --> 00:05:41,860
on the Qinghai-Tibet Highway.

58
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,520
You walked out yourself?

59
00:05:45,770 --> 00:05:47,230
You're really something.

60
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:48,230
Go home first.

61
00:05:50,930 --> 00:05:51,659
You need

62
00:05:52,220 --> 00:05:53,280
to give me the money

63
00:05:53,890 --> 00:05:54,810
we agreed on.

64
00:05:55,510 --> 00:05:56,170
What money?

65
00:06:00,190 --> 00:06:00,830
My wages.

66
00:06:02,420 --> 00:06:03,330
Wages?

67
00:06:04,330 --> 00:06:05,860
The wages were all settled.

68
00:06:05,870 --> 00:06:07,060
The people who went in with you

69
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:07,740
were out

70
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:09,120
by the 3rd day.

71
00:06:09,220 --> 00:06:10,750
The wages were all settled.

72
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:12,270
Guo Shun!

73
00:06:12,370 --> 00:06:13,830
Are you trying to stiff me?

74
00:06:14,330 --> 00:06:15,560
I skinned 30 Tibetan antelopes!

75
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,360
Keep shouting

76
00:06:17,540 --> 00:06:19,270
and you’ll get the police here!

77
00:06:30,450 --> 00:06:31,300
This Bolamula

78
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:32,790
really toughens people.

79
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:34,659
You even dared

80
00:06:34,659 --> 00:06:36,100
to pull a weapon on me.

81
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:44,450
Didn’t we agree before you set off?

82
00:06:44,980 --> 00:06:47,250
Seven yuan per pelt.

83
00:06:47,870 --> 00:06:49,200
I need to wait for the...

84
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:52,370
I need to wait for the boss

85
00:06:52,370 --> 00:06:53,370
to give me a number

86
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,830
before I can pay you.

87
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:56,710
But the boss isn’t out yet.

88
00:06:56,930 --> 00:06:57,590
So if you say

89
00:06:57,620 --> 00:06:59,500
you skinned 30,000 Tibetan antelopes,

90
00:06:59,500 --> 00:06:59,950
should I just

91
00:06:59,950 --> 00:07:01,300
pay you for that?

92
00:07:01,390 --> 00:07:02,330
Am I stupid?

93
00:07:03,330 --> 00:07:03,890
Guo.

94
00:07:04,630 --> 00:07:05,250
Mr. Guo.

95
00:07:06,060 --> 00:07:07,830
This has blown up too big.

96
00:07:08,190 --> 00:07:09,720
People have even died.

97
00:07:14,190 --> 00:07:14,620
Guo.

98
00:07:16,190 --> 00:07:17,360
I'm begging you.

99
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:19,660
Please.

100
00:07:19,770 --> 00:07:21,030
Just give me some money

101
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,420
and I can run away.

102
00:07:22,660 --> 00:07:23,860
I'm begging you, Guo.

103
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:24,810
Please.

104
00:07:25,390 --> 00:07:26,420
What's the rush?

105
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,330
I didn't say I wouldn't pay you.

106
00:07:29,860 --> 00:07:30,570
Once the boss is out,

107
00:07:30,570 --> 00:07:31,900
I'll give you the money.

108
00:07:41,220 --> 00:07:42,550
How long will that take?

109
00:07:43,430 --> 00:07:44,680
You have to let the boss

110
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,930
lie low for a while.

111
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:50,860
Bai Ji.

112
00:07:51,830 --> 00:07:53,230
How come you fell asleep?

113
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:54,270
Come on. Go home.

114
00:07:54,270 --> 00:07:55,200
Go home to sleep.

115
00:07:58,930 --> 00:07:59,600
I'm hungry.

116
00:08:01,390 --> 00:08:02,600
Is there any food?

117
00:08:11,690 --> 00:08:12,750
This isn't enough.

118
00:08:12,830 --> 00:08:14,160
I still need two pieces.

119
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:15,810
Oh, Guo Shun.

120
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:17,070
You’re like a big pot

121
00:08:17,070 --> 00:08:18,000
trying to fit everything

122
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:18,810
in your mouth.

123
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,190
Don't be too greedy.

124
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:23,040
Be careful—you might die before you spend it.

125
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:23,890
I know, I know.

126
00:08:24,190 --> 00:08:26,050
You guys asked for this in a hurry.

127
00:08:26,420 --> 00:08:27,560
This is a rush fee.

128
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:28,750
Back then we...

129
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,370
What are you doing?

130
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:31,600
Is it done?

131
00:08:31,690 --> 00:08:32,820
He wants more money.

132
00:08:33,530 --> 00:08:34,330
How much more?

133
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,320
How will you explain this to the boss?

134
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:40,390
Explain what?

135
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:41,030
There's only

136
00:08:41,030 --> 00:08:42,390
a woman there in Meiseng Village.

137
00:08:42,390 --> 00:08:43,320
If this gets held up

138
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,270
over 200 yuan,

139
00:08:44,370 --> 00:08:45,510
you can explain it to the boss yourself.

140
00:08:45,510 --> 00:08:45,910
Move!

141
00:08:48,910 --> 00:08:49,480
Hurry up.

142
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:51,450
That's more like it.

143
00:09:02,620 --> 00:09:03,220
Here.

144
00:09:03,460 --> 00:09:04,220
This little bit?

145
00:09:04,220 --> 00:09:04,960
Is it enough?

146
00:09:05,770 --> 00:09:07,670
This stuff is powerful.

147
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:10,170
We use it to blast mines.

148
00:09:10,460 --> 00:09:12,320
It's enough to blow up a building.

149
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,130
Bai Ji?

150
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:29,050
Where have you been running wild this time?

151
00:09:29,050 --> 00:09:30,710
You’re filthy, like a marmot.

152
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:39,200
Bai Ji!

153
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,010
Where have you been these days?

154
00:09:41,010 --> 00:09:41,460
Stop! Stop!

155
00:09:41,460 --> 00:09:41,960
I was just about to look for you.

156
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:42,620
Stop! Stop!

157
00:09:42,870 --> 00:09:43,330
Get off!

158
00:09:43,370 --> 00:09:43,830
Get off!

159
00:09:44,370 --> 00:09:45,010
Bai Ji!

160
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:46,500
Bai Ji!

161
00:09:48,010 --> 00:09:49,320
Be nice to Meiduo!

162
00:09:49,820 --> 00:09:51,080
Don't let her get hurt!

163
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:54,620
What's wrong with Bai Ji?

164
00:09:54,620 --> 00:09:55,510
I don't know.

165
00:09:56,390 --> 00:09:57,290
Who is Meiduo?

166
00:09:57,370 --> 00:09:58,550
My motorcycle.

167
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:12,050
Why is there not a single vegetable?

168
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:13,980
What’s so good about eating grass?

169
00:10:17,250 --> 00:10:18,380
Well, watch the pot.

170
00:10:18,410 --> 00:10:20,540
I'll go see what vegetables I can find.

171
00:11:05,030 --> 00:11:06,230
Why haven't you left?

172
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:08,740
Why are you back?

173
00:11:11,650 --> 00:11:12,340
We eat

174
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,640
so we won’t be hungry.

175
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:16,620
We drink milk to stay strong and healthy.

176
00:11:17,220 --> 00:11:18,820
We wear clothes to keep warm.

177
00:11:19,630 --> 00:11:20,480
We chant prayers

178
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:22,280
for good fortune and happiness.

179
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:24,830
Bai, what do you think

180
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:26,510
people live for?

181
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:28,080
To beat you up.

182
00:11:28,860 --> 00:11:30,370
Don’t learn from Zhacuo.

183
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:31,200
Say it or don’t.

184
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,000
Whatever.

185
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:37,770
I had a dream.

186
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,520
What did you dream about?

187
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:41,790
I dreamed

188
00:11:42,290 --> 00:11:43,200
I got a permanent position

189
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:45,200
and was working for the government.

190
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,730
Sounds like a dream you'd have.

191
00:11:48,740 --> 00:11:50,120
If you want a permanent position,

192
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:51,240
going home and sleeping

193
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:52,770
would get you there faster.

194
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,410
And in the dream,

195
00:11:59,170 --> 00:12:01,100
I was wearing a police uniform too.

196
00:12:02,790 --> 00:12:04,250
You dreamed you were a cop?

197
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:07,050
No.

198
00:12:07,980 --> 00:12:08,290
In the dream,

199
00:12:08,290 --> 00:12:10,130
the Economic Development Zone was established,

200
00:12:10,130 --> 00:12:11,790
and I was the deputy director.

201
00:12:13,670 --> 00:12:16,070
Then why were you wearing a police uniform?

202
00:12:16,650 --> 00:12:17,380
I don't know.

203
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:17,790
Maybe it's because

204
00:12:17,790 --> 00:12:19,390
I always see you wearing one.

205
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:22,440
I just feel like people with government jobs

206
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:23,770
all have a uniform.

207
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:26,850
Just like how every Tibetan

208
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:27,980
has a knife

209
00:12:27,980 --> 00:12:29,030
of their own.

210
00:12:30,910 --> 00:12:31,670
I can’t really explain it.

211
00:12:31,670 --> 00:12:32,800
You know what I mean.

212
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:34,630
I don't.

213
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,360
Having a permanent position means wearing a uniform?

214
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:40,360
The Captain doesn't have a uniform.

215
00:12:46,130 --> 00:12:47,730
I also dreamed of Dongzhiba.

216
00:12:50,550 --> 00:12:52,550
He was wearing a police uniform too,

217
00:12:52,670 --> 00:12:54,200
and he looked really happy.

218
00:13:04,050 --> 00:13:04,870
Ju!

219
00:13:05,870 --> 00:13:06,890
Ju!

220
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,100
Bai Ju!

221
00:13:18,770 --> 00:13:19,650
Ju!

222
00:13:21,650 --> 00:13:22,870
Ju!

223
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:25,320
Bai Ju!

224
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:29,010
Do you think

225
00:13:29,130 --> 00:13:31,530
the Captain would agree to let me come back?

226
00:13:31,820 --> 00:13:32,650
Do you think

227
00:13:32,750 --> 00:13:35,080
he’d agree to let me go into the mountains?

228
00:13:38,050 --> 00:13:39,360
I get what you mean.

229
00:13:39,460 --> 00:13:41,320
Looks like I don’t stand a chance.

230
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,030
What I mean is,

231
00:13:44,150 --> 00:13:45,100
there’s no point talking about this

232
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:46,100
between the two of us.

233
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:47,170
You might as well wait for the Captain to come back

234
00:13:47,170 --> 00:13:48,370
and ask him yourself.

235
00:13:51,550 --> 00:13:52,530
Besides,

236
00:13:52,770 --> 00:13:53,750
how can you be so sure

237
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:54,700
I can't get into the mountains?

238
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:56,200
If he were going to let you go,

239
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,150
you would’ve gone in

240
00:13:57,150 --> 00:13:58,600
with He Qingyuan and the others this time.

241
00:13:58,600 --> 00:13:59,700
They were going to look for your brother.

242
00:13:59,700 --> 00:14:01,760
You must be more worried than anyone.

243
00:14:08,510 --> 00:14:09,440
I feel like...

244
00:14:11,170 --> 00:14:12,550
I'm worried sick.

245
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:14,920
What's wrong?

246
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:16,710
I think I hear

247
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:18,030
Bai Ji calling me,

248
00:14:19,770 --> 00:14:21,430
calling me "Ju" over and over.

249
00:14:22,370 --> 00:14:23,630
Maybe he’s missing you

250
00:14:23,650 --> 00:14:24,980
somewhere in Bolamula.

251
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:26,250
The voice in his heart

252
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:27,220
crossed the snow mountains

253
00:14:27,220 --> 00:14:28,360
and reached you.

254
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:29,150
Really?

255
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:33,530
It sounds like

256
00:14:34,620 --> 00:14:36,150
he's shouting for me to run.

257
00:14:38,390 --> 00:14:40,390
He's even calling me by my full name.

258
00:14:45,770 --> 00:14:46,410
That's strange.

259
00:14:46,410 --> 00:14:47,370
Why can I hear

260
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:48,560
Bai Ji's voice too?

261
00:14:48,790 --> 00:14:50,240
Is he missing me too?

262
00:14:55,050 --> 00:14:56,510
Ju!

263
00:14:57,170 --> 00:14:58,290
Ju!

264
00:14:58,530 --> 00:14:58,930
Bai Ji?

265
00:14:59,000 --> 00:14:59,670
Run!

266
00:15:00,130 --> 00:15:00,530
Bai Ji!

267
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:01,290
Run!

268
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:04,370
Someone's going to blow up the Mountain Patrol!

269
00:15:04,370 --> 00:15:06,370
They're going to blow you up!

270
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:16,440
Bai Ji!

271
00:15:16,890 --> 00:15:18,030
You bastard!

272
00:15:18,510 --> 00:15:20,480
Where have you been these past few days?

273
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:20,960
Hurry!

274
00:15:21,370 --> 00:15:22,550
Hurry!

275
00:15:22,650 --> 00:15:24,290
Run!

276
00:15:24,390 --> 00:15:25,600
There's...

277
00:15:25,770 --> 00:15:26,500
What did you say?

278
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:28,630
Danger!

279
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:32,130
Ju!

280
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:33,170
Ju!

281
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:36,370
Ju!

282
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:42,600
Bai Ji!

283
00:15:43,220 --> 00:15:43,740
Ju?

284
00:15:44,630 --> 00:15:45,560
Don't come over!

285
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:46,860
Don't come over!

286
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:48,340
Someone blew up the warehouse!

287
00:15:48,340 --> 00:15:49,470
It must be poachers!

288
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:50,430
Don't come over!

289
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:50,970
Let's go!

290
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:00,390
Mountain Patrol!

291
00:16:00,390 --> 00:16:00,910
Go! Go!

292
00:16:02,980 --> 00:16:04,110
Hurry up and load it!

293
00:16:05,370 --> 00:16:06,750
Hurry up! Hurry!

294
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,000
Where's your gun?

295
00:16:10,530 --> 00:16:12,330
They took it into the mountains!

296
00:16:12,580 --> 00:16:13,840
The Captain's gun should still be here.

297
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:14,670
Let's go!

298
00:16:15,220 --> 00:16:16,130
Hurry! Hurry!

299
00:16:16,390 --> 00:16:17,480
Hurry! Hurry!

300
00:16:17,650 --> 00:16:18,510
What's happening?

301
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:19,500
What's going on?

302
00:16:21,890 --> 00:16:23,690
They're here to steal the pelts!

303
00:16:23,860 --> 00:16:24,870
And they have guns!

304
00:16:24,870 --> 00:16:25,580
Got it. Got it.

305
00:16:25,580 --> 00:16:26,750
Watch out, everyone! Get down!

306
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:27,510
Get down!

307
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:39,080
What should we do?

308
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:40,400
Wait a second.

309
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:41,740
Come here! Come here!

310
00:16:41,860 --> 00:16:43,080
Pick some stones! Pick some stones!

311
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:43,630
-Okay.
-Okay.

312
00:16:43,630 --> 00:16:45,080
On the roof! On the roof!

313
00:16:45,130 --> 00:16:45,630
Got it!

314
00:16:46,290 --> 00:16:48,630
One, two, three!

315
00:17:31,250 --> 00:17:31,810
Come on!

316
00:17:31,980 --> 00:17:33,680
Load it up! Hurry! Let's move out.

317
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:34,380
Got it!

318
00:17:34,810 --> 00:17:36,070
Take two more bundles!

319
00:18:05,770 --> 00:18:06,880
Bastards!

320
00:18:17,810 --> 00:18:18,480
Sangba!

321
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,350
Hurry up!

322
00:18:28,570 --> 00:18:29,300
Give it to me!

323
00:18:38,050 --> 00:18:38,720
Brothers!

324
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:39,700
Come on!

325
00:18:50,740 --> 00:18:52,030
Bai Ji, come here!

326
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,290
Come with me to the Public Security Bureau

327
00:18:53,290 --> 00:18:55,150
and explain everything clearly!

328
00:18:58,400 --> 00:18:59,290
Ju!

329
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:02,940
I... I...

330
00:19:03,030 --> 00:19:05,400
I didn't kill anyone!

331
00:19:11,070 --> 00:19:12,750
I know you didn't kill anyone!

332
00:19:13,790 --> 00:19:15,120
Come back with me first!

333
00:19:17,330 --> 00:19:19,160
I—I'm not going back!

334
00:19:22,110 --> 00:19:23,640
I didn't kill anyone!

335
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:25,200
I won't go back!

336
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:26,640
Stop!

337
00:19:26,740 --> 00:19:28,250
I didn't kill anyone!

338
00:19:28,350 --> 00:19:29,030
Come back!

339
00:19:29,790 --> 00:19:30,550
Bai Ji!

340
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:33,980
Bai Ji! Bai Ji!

341
00:19:37,790 --> 00:19:38,440
Come back!

342
00:19:55,350 --> 00:19:56,030
Hello?

343
00:19:56,140 --> 00:19:56,770
Sangba?

344
00:19:57,700 --> 00:19:58,500
You're back.

345
00:19:59,070 --> 00:19:59,920
I just got back.

346
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:00,880
Tell Bai Ju to drive

347
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:01,940
to Wangmu's place.

348
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:03,890
I bought some food for the team.

349
00:20:04,290 --> 00:20:05,510
Captain, I'm afraid she can't do that.

350
00:20:05,510 --> 00:20:06,500
The warehouse just got blown up.

351
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:07,900
And we caught two people.

352
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:08,530
What?

353
00:20:09,220 --> 00:20:10,590
The warehouse got blown up?

354
00:20:10,590 --> 00:20:11,050
Hello?

355
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:12,740
Why did you lock up that stupid gun of yours?

356
00:20:12,740 --> 00:20:13,900
All you do is lock it!

357
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:14,660
Always locking it!

358
00:20:14,660 --> 00:20:16,090
Don't you know how to maintain it properly?

359
00:20:16,090 --> 00:20:17,050
The magazine’s all rusty!

360
00:20:17,050 --> 00:20:18,160
It was so hard to use!

361
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:19,400
There were just a few lousy bullets—

362
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:20,130
why hide them

363
00:20:20,160 --> 00:20:21,010
under your pillow?

364
00:20:21,010 --> 00:20:23,010
Isn't it uncomfortable to sleep on?

365
00:20:35,740 --> 00:20:37,750
Duojie, Sangba,

366
00:20:38,050 --> 00:20:39,400
we brought over the wood

367
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:40,610
to repair the house.

368
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:41,640
Okay, thank you.

369
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:42,660
Thanks.

370
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:44,460
You're welcome. We're leaving now.

371
00:20:44,460 --> 00:20:45,060
Thank you.

372
00:20:45,140 --> 00:20:46,110
No problem. Bye.

373
00:21:01,180 --> 00:21:01,750
You haven’t used a bow in a while,

374
00:21:01,750 --> 00:21:02,720
have you?

375
00:21:04,740 --> 00:21:05,940
Your aim is terrible.

376
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:07,970
You even let one escape.

377
00:21:09,350 --> 00:21:10,000
No matter how fast an arrow is,

378
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,660
it’s not faster than a bullet.

379
00:21:13,110 --> 00:21:14,010
Next time in the mountains,

380
00:21:14,010 --> 00:21:15,140
everyone gets a gun—

381
00:21:15,750 --> 00:21:17,150
just you with a bow. Fine.

382
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:18,460
Okay,

383
00:21:18,530 --> 00:21:19,220
no problem.

384
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:20,380
I used to be first place

385
00:21:20,380 --> 00:21:21,840
in archery competitions.

386
00:21:26,010 --> 00:21:26,540
Captain,

387
00:21:27,010 --> 00:21:28,480
it was all thanks to Bai this time.

388
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:29,850
My shooting’s not bad,

389
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:31,560
but it can’t compare to hers.

390
00:21:33,270 --> 00:21:33,920
Really?

391
00:21:34,770 --> 00:21:35,250
Really.

392
00:21:35,350 --> 00:21:36,590
One piece of gold

393
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:37,750
is worth more than a pile of iron.

394
00:21:37,750 --> 00:21:39,420
If Bai goes into the mountains,

395
00:21:39,420 --> 00:21:40,950
she'll be worth 10 Zhacuos.

396
00:21:42,750 --> 00:21:43,830
One Zhacuo

397
00:21:43,920 --> 00:21:45,450
is already enough trouble.

398
00:21:45,980 --> 00:21:46,590
I’m talking about

399
00:21:46,590 --> 00:21:47,750
her accuracy.

400
00:21:47,850 --> 00:21:48,850
She never misses.

401
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:51,590
In that case,

402
00:21:51,700 --> 00:21:53,300
she’d be better at poaching.

403
00:21:57,050 --> 00:21:58,250
I'm a police officer.

404
00:21:58,750 --> 00:21:59,750
Back in the police academy,

405
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:01,750
my shooting scores were excellent.

406
00:22:02,660 --> 00:22:03,980
Okay, okay. I got it.

407
00:22:04,810 --> 00:22:06,210
You’re a police officer—

408
00:22:06,380 --> 00:22:07,510
pretty impressive.

409
00:22:17,590 --> 00:22:18,510
Easy, easy.

410
00:22:18,850 --> 00:22:19,590
Feeling the pain now?

411
00:22:19,590 --> 00:22:20,240
Bear with it.

412
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:21,040
Get in the car.

413
00:22:21,090 --> 00:22:21,690
Come here!

414
00:22:23,310 --> 00:22:23,770
Get in.

415
00:22:35,980 --> 00:22:37,040
Aren't you coming?

416
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:38,740
You go.

417
00:22:39,290 --> 00:22:40,070
Going back to the bureau like this

418
00:22:40,070 --> 00:22:41,270
is too embarrassing.

419
00:22:42,050 --> 00:22:43,000
If you go into the mountains,

420
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,140
you'll only get dirtier

421
00:22:44,140 --> 00:22:45,110
and look even worse.

422
00:22:45,110 --> 00:22:46,180
That's different.

423
00:22:49,030 --> 00:22:49,640
Let's go.

424
00:22:50,380 --> 00:22:52,200
You can take a shower at the bureau.

425
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:55,330
How long has it been since the last time you took a shower?

426
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:57,180
Ten days or twenty days

427
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:58,420
makes no difference.

428
00:23:00,010 --> 00:23:00,590
Bai Ju.

429
00:23:08,270 --> 00:23:09,670
Are you still not going to

430
00:23:09,750 --> 00:23:11,610
tell Director Zhang about Bai Ji?

431
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:16,180
Before, it was fine not to tell her because you were afraid

432
00:23:16,180 --> 00:23:17,050
she’d worry.

433
00:23:17,810 --> 00:23:18,140
But now that

434
00:23:18,140 --> 00:23:19,590
Bai Ji has come out of the Uninhabited Zone,

435
00:23:19,590 --> 00:23:21,720
it wouldn’t be right to keep it secret.

436
00:23:22,090 --> 00:23:22,900
Your mother should know

437
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:24,180
what happened to him,

438
00:23:27,290 --> 00:23:29,020
and also about your situation.

439
00:23:29,090 --> 00:23:31,820
It would be a good chance to talk about it with her.

440
00:23:32,180 --> 00:23:33,400
You can ask her

441
00:23:34,250 --> 00:23:37,110
whether she agrees to you going into the mountains.

442
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:45,090
Nima.

443
00:23:45,660 --> 00:23:46,460
Nima.

444
00:23:47,030 --> 00:23:48,360
Don’t be angry anymore.

445
00:23:49,240 --> 00:23:50,380
Given the situation back then,

446
00:23:50,380 --> 00:23:51,070
I really had no choice.

447
00:23:51,070 --> 00:23:52,480
I could only leave it there.

448
00:23:52,480 --> 00:23:52,940
You...

449
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:55,000
I was wrong, okay?

450
00:23:55,090 --> 00:23:56,030
Don't be angry.

451
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:57,460
Meiduo isn't lost.

452
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:57,980
Look,

453
00:23:58,070 --> 00:23:59,700
her mirror is right here.

454
00:24:00,030 --> 00:24:01,000
She’s in Meiseng Village now,

455
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:01,920
safe and sound.

456
00:24:02,010 --> 00:24:02,770
My sister will definitely

457
00:24:02,770 --> 00:24:03,900
take good care of it.

458
00:24:04,270 --> 00:24:04,960
If you don't believe me,

459
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:06,560
you can go pick it up anytime.

460
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:07,500
I promise.

461
00:24:07,590 --> 00:24:08,680
Why don't you go yourself?

462
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:09,160
I...

463
00:24:11,250 --> 00:24:12,050
Seriously.

464
00:24:13,610 --> 00:24:14,810
I can go.

465
00:24:15,570 --> 00:24:16,310
But my sister...

466
00:24:16,310 --> 00:24:17,610
is really angry right now.

467
00:24:17,610 --> 00:24:18,350
If I go there now,

468
00:24:18,350 --> 00:24:19,350
she'll definitely beat me up.

469
00:24:19,350 --> 00:24:19,880
Alright.

470
00:24:20,090 --> 00:24:21,890
Stop waving that mirror around.

471
00:24:22,050 --> 00:24:22,660
The reflection

472
00:24:22,660 --> 00:24:24,320
could melt the snow mountain.

473
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:26,660
The sacred mountain will get angry, understand?

474
00:24:26,660 --> 00:24:27,860
Don't wave it around.

475
00:24:28,590 --> 00:24:29,810
Then let me smear some cow dung on it.

476
00:24:29,810 --> 00:24:30,850
Don't joke around.

477
00:24:30,850 --> 00:24:31,250
Bai Ji!

478
00:24:31,330 --> 00:24:32,200
Don't break it.

479
00:24:32,610 --> 00:24:33,420
It's okay. Let me smear some cow dung on it.

480
00:24:33,420 --> 00:24:34,310
Give it to me. Give it to me.

481
00:24:34,310 --> 00:24:34,940
Don't break it.

482
00:24:34,940 --> 00:24:36,140
Let me smear some cow dung on it.

483
00:24:36,140 --> 00:24:36,870
Give it to me!

484
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:37,880
If you promise not to be mad, I'll give it to you.

485
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:38,460
Come on. Give it to me.

486
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:39,140
I'll give it to you when you're not mad.

487
00:24:39,140 --> 00:24:39,850
Give it to me. Don't break it.

488
00:24:39,850 --> 00:24:41,980
I'll give it to you when you're not mad.

489
00:24:42,830 --> 00:24:44,290
I'm going away for a while.

490
00:24:44,850 --> 00:24:45,640
I don’t know

491
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:46,940
when I’ll be back.

492
00:24:47,330 --> 00:24:48,750
I’m leaving Meiduo in your care,

493
00:24:48,750 --> 00:24:49,220
bro.

494
00:24:49,980 --> 00:24:51,110
Where are you going?

495
00:24:51,830 --> 00:24:53,290
To herd sheep for someone?

496
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:55,280
I'm going to plant trees.

497
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,260
Does our county...

498
00:25:01,350 --> 00:25:02,640
even have that kind of work?

499
00:25:02,640 --> 00:25:03,640
Not in our county.

500
00:25:04,750 --> 00:25:06,200
I’m going to Gansu to plant trees.

501
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:06,750
Gansu?

502
00:25:07,250 --> 00:25:07,910
So far away?

503
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:09,700
To do something big,

504
00:25:09,920 --> 00:25:11,530
you have to travel far, far away.

505
00:25:11,530 --> 00:25:12,400
Got it, bro?

506
00:25:16,350 --> 00:25:17,660
How are you getting there?

507
00:25:17,660 --> 00:25:18,790
I'm not going alone.

508
00:25:19,160 --> 00:25:20,680
There’s a vehicle taking us.

509
00:25:20,680 --> 00:25:21,940
First we go to Tianduo,

510
00:25:22,290 --> 00:25:25,790
then take a long-distance bus from there to the provincial capital,

511
00:25:25,790 --> 00:25:27,830
and finally a train to Gansu.

512
00:25:27,940 --> 00:25:29,800
That’s not even the destination.

513
00:25:29,980 --> 00:25:30,920
After arriving in Gansu,

514
00:25:30,920 --> 00:25:33,180
we still need to take a long-distance bus

515
00:25:33,850 --> 00:25:34,290
to...

516
00:25:35,160 --> 00:25:36,090
Yuzhong County.

517
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:38,660
I heard the altitude there

518
00:25:39,070 --> 00:25:40,470
is much lower than Mazhi,

519
00:25:41,250 --> 00:25:44,240
and the oxygen there is so rich it could make you dizzy.

520
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:46,100
I don't know what that feels like.

521
00:25:46,590 --> 00:25:47,850
It's probably like

522
00:25:47,960 --> 00:25:49,560
drinking Mom's barley wine.

523
00:25:59,740 --> 00:26:01,270
I want to get drunk once too.

524
00:26:06,590 --> 00:26:07,270
Gansu?

525
00:26:08,030 --> 00:26:08,790
Count me in.

526
00:26:22,510 --> 00:26:23,050
Bai Shao.

527
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:38,020
Hello, beautiful.

528
00:26:38,070 --> 00:26:39,070
Hello, sir.

529
00:26:39,180 --> 00:26:39,610
How

530
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:40,900
may I help you?

531
00:26:44,830 --> 00:26:46,490
I'm making a deposit. Thanks.

532
00:26:47,700 --> 00:26:48,240
Okay.

533
00:27:06,010 --> 00:27:06,810
Hurry, hurry.

534
00:27:09,680 --> 00:27:11,240
I told you

535
00:27:11,330 --> 00:27:11,900
you need to wear

536
00:27:11,900 --> 00:27:13,220
a cotton jacket here.

537
00:27:13,740 --> 00:27:14,330
This is already

538
00:27:14,330 --> 00:27:15,510
my thickest coat.

539
00:27:17,010 --> 00:27:17,440
Shao.

540
00:27:19,530 --> 00:27:20,010
What?

541
00:27:29,270 --> 00:27:29,740
Shao.

542
00:27:30,610 --> 00:27:31,940
What do you want?

543
00:27:32,180 --> 00:27:32,910
I'm working.

544
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:33,440
If my boss finds out,

545
00:27:33,440 --> 00:27:34,770
he'll dock my pay again.

546
00:27:35,900 --> 00:27:37,230
What are you looking at?

547
00:27:37,250 --> 00:27:38,000
Look at that fool.

548
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:38,900
Isn't he cold?

549
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:40,860
I don't think you're cold either.

550
00:27:40,940 --> 00:27:42,570
I'm going back if you have nothing to say.

551
00:27:42,570 --> 00:27:43,680
Shao, come with me.

552
00:27:49,770 --> 00:27:50,380
Shao.

553
00:27:51,940 --> 00:27:52,420
There's something

554
00:27:52,420 --> 00:27:53,530
I need to tell you.

555
00:27:56,050 --> 00:27:57,380
Mom doesn't know it yet.

556
00:27:57,770 --> 00:27:58,250
But...

557
00:27:58,350 --> 00:27:58,810
but I...

558
00:27:58,900 --> 00:28:00,830
don't know how to bring it up to her.

559
00:28:02,590 --> 00:28:04,180
I can't keep quiet...

560
00:28:04,290 --> 00:28:04,960
about this.

561
00:28:05,920 --> 00:28:06,640
I can’t...

562
00:28:06,740 --> 00:28:07,940
just hide it forever.

563
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:11,680
But I don't want Mom to worry.

564
00:28:13,290 --> 00:28:13,830
Even though

565
00:28:13,830 --> 00:28:15,140
Mom is more open-minded

566
00:28:15,140 --> 00:28:16,140
than most people,

567
00:28:18,090 --> 00:28:18,750
this...

568
00:28:19,960 --> 00:28:20,940
this thing...

569
00:28:23,740 --> 00:28:24,200
It...

570
00:28:24,750 --> 00:28:26,720
It's a matter of principle.

571
00:28:27,220 --> 00:28:27,480
I...

572
00:28:27,500 --> 00:28:28,700
How far along are you?

573
00:28:31,270 --> 00:28:32,510
Bai Ju, don't be scared.

574
00:28:32,510 --> 00:28:33,510
Tell me the truth.

575
00:28:33,550 --> 00:28:34,050
Is that guy

576
00:28:34,050 --> 00:28:35,580
from your Mountain Patrol?

577
00:28:37,380 --> 00:28:38,290
Bai Shao!

578
00:28:38,510 --> 00:28:39,420
What have you been thinking about

579
00:28:39,420 --> 00:28:40,310
all day?

580
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:43,480
You’re disgusting!

581
00:28:44,830 --> 00:28:45,610
That’s not it?

582
00:28:45,610 --> 00:28:46,590
No!

583
00:28:48,530 --> 00:28:50,010
Then what is it?

584
00:28:50,350 --> 00:28:51,550
You scared me.

585
00:28:56,200 --> 00:28:56,790
That brat Bai Ji

586
00:28:56,790 --> 00:28:57,920
is way too reckless!

587
00:28:58,160 --> 00:28:59,690
Risking his life for money!

588
00:29:03,350 --> 00:29:04,680
And you’re just as bold,

589
00:29:04,770 --> 00:29:05,290
keeping something this serious

590
00:29:05,290 --> 00:29:06,310
from Mom.

591
00:29:07,420 --> 00:29:08,820
I was afraid she’d worry.

592
00:29:09,420 --> 00:29:10,310
Even if she’d known back then,

593
00:29:10,310 --> 00:29:11,570
all she could’ve done was worry.

594
00:29:11,570 --> 00:29:12,180
Of course,

595
00:29:12,770 --> 00:29:14,300
you’ve got all the excuses.

596
00:29:15,530 --> 00:29:16,210
And after Bai Ji came out,

597
00:29:16,210 --> 00:29:17,340
he didn’t come home.

598
00:29:18,270 --> 00:29:20,160
We can’t let him keep running wild.

599
00:29:20,160 --> 00:29:21,420
He got lucky this time.

600
00:29:21,510 --> 00:29:22,200
Next time, who knows

601
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:23,200
what will happen?

602
00:29:28,420 --> 00:29:29,090
Shao,

603
00:29:29,850 --> 00:29:31,290
what about Mom?

604
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:32,570
What do you think?

605
00:29:34,290 --> 00:29:36,420
I'll tell her when I get home from work.

606
00:29:37,050 --> 00:29:38,780
It's better for you to tell her.

607
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:43,500
No one ever comes to me with good news.

608
00:29:43,900 --> 00:29:44,830
Wait for me here.

609
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,770
Based on the on-site investigation,

610
00:29:51,770 --> 00:29:52,790
the explosion was caused by

611
00:29:52,790 --> 00:29:54,520
ammonium nitrate explosives.

612
00:29:54,900 --> 00:29:56,750
The main structure of the building remains intact,

613
00:29:56,750 --> 00:29:58,010
with only a two-by-two-meter breach

614
00:29:58,010 --> 00:29:59,500
in the exterior wall.

615
00:30:00,740 --> 00:30:01,880
According to the suspect

616
00:30:01,880 --> 00:30:03,460
brought back by Deputy County Mayor Duo,

617
00:30:03,460 --> 00:30:05,030
it was retaliation by a poaching gang

618
00:30:05,030 --> 00:30:06,740
against the Mountain Patrol,

619
00:30:07,160 --> 00:30:09,290
attempting to seize their pelts back.

620
00:30:09,380 --> 00:30:10,840
We found a walking tractor

621
00:30:10,880 --> 00:30:12,570
driven by the fugitive suspect

622
00:30:12,570 --> 00:30:13,010
on a rural road

623
00:30:13,010 --> 00:30:13,920
3 kilometers

624
00:30:14,010 --> 00:30:15,050
from Meiseng Village

625
00:30:15,050 --> 00:30:16,000
and are currently conducting a search

626
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,380
in the surrounding area.

627
00:30:17,380 --> 00:30:17,920
Also,

628
00:30:18,030 --> 00:30:19,550
Guo Shun, the auto repair shop owner

629
00:30:19,550 --> 00:30:21,210
who supplied the explosives—

630
00:30:21,640 --> 00:30:22,920
when we went to arrest him,

631
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:23,980
the shop was closed

632
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:25,330
and he had already fled.

633
00:30:25,440 --> 00:30:26,200
The bureau

634
00:30:26,290 --> 00:30:27,180
has circulated his description

635
00:30:27,180 --> 00:30:28,160
to checkpoints

636
00:30:28,250 --> 00:30:30,180
along the Qinghai-Tibet Highway.

637
00:30:30,570 --> 00:30:31,680
Fortunately,

638
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:33,290
the explosion didn't cause

639
00:30:33,290 --> 00:30:34,680
any casualties.

640
00:30:35,510 --> 00:30:36,970
What about the aftermath?

641
00:30:37,330 --> 00:30:38,330
County Mayor Lin.

642
00:30:39,510 --> 00:30:40,550
I have already applied to the Finance Bureau

643
00:30:40,550 --> 00:30:41,290
for the repair costs

644
00:30:41,290 --> 00:30:42,590
of the warehouse.

645
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:43,760
It's not much.

646
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:46,220
It hasn't been long.

647
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:47,290
In quick succession,

648
00:30:47,290 --> 00:30:48,440
a patrol member was sacrificed

649
00:30:48,440 --> 00:30:50,100
and the warehouse was bombed.

650
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:52,460
The security situation is very grim.

651
00:30:52,480 --> 00:30:53,410
Secretary Chen.

652
00:30:53,700 --> 00:30:54,700
County Mayor Lin.

653
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:57,200
I request that the Mountain Patrol

654
00:30:57,200 --> 00:30:57,920
be fully equipped

655
00:30:57,920 --> 00:30:58,940
with semi-automatic rifles

656
00:30:58,940 --> 00:31:00,270
and 7.62mm ammunition.

657
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:01,610
I remember,

658
00:31:02,220 --> 00:31:03,420
didn't you seize

659
00:31:03,850 --> 00:31:05,310
guns and ammunition?

660
00:31:06,700 --> 00:31:08,750
Most of the guns and ammunition we seized

661
00:31:08,750 --> 00:31:09,940
were handed over.

662
00:31:10,810 --> 00:31:11,830
Every time we go into the mountains,

663
00:31:11,830 --> 00:31:13,430
we have to count our bullets.

664
00:31:14,110 --> 00:31:14,770
If it weren't for the marksmanship

665
00:31:14,770 --> 00:31:15,770
of the officer guarding the station,

666
00:31:15,770 --> 00:31:16,770
the consequences

667
00:31:16,920 --> 00:31:18,650
would have been unimaginable.

668
00:31:20,420 --> 00:31:21,140
I apply for

669
00:31:21,810 --> 00:31:22,550
full usage rights

670
00:31:22,550 --> 00:31:23,570
to the seized guns

671
00:31:23,680 --> 00:31:24,880
and ammunition.

672
00:31:25,750 --> 00:31:27,080
We must take the request

673
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:28,640
made by Comrade Duojie seriously.

674
00:31:28,640 --> 00:31:30,100
What does everyone think?

675
00:31:31,420 --> 00:31:32,380
Regarding the full usage rights

676
00:31:32,380 --> 00:31:33,770
for the guns and ammunition,

677
00:31:33,770 --> 00:31:34,460
I agree.

678
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:36,380
However,

679
00:31:36,480 --> 00:31:37,680
after this incident,

680
00:31:37,940 --> 00:31:39,000
I personally think

681
00:31:39,530 --> 00:31:41,790
it is inappropriate for female comrades

682
00:31:42,750 --> 00:31:44,480
to stay in the Mountain Patrol.

683
00:31:44,750 --> 00:31:46,110
Could we deploy males

684
00:31:46,460 --> 00:31:47,720
to the Mountain Patrol

685
00:31:47,750 --> 00:31:49,270
to guide the work?

686
00:31:52,090 --> 00:31:52,950
How about this?

687
00:31:53,270 --> 00:31:54,330
I'll go back and see

688
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:56,090
about sending a male over.

689
00:31:56,090 --> 00:31:58,290
If Deputy County Mayor Duojie needs it,

690
00:31:58,310 --> 00:31:59,970
I can add someone from my side.

691
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:01,770
No need for more people.

692
00:32:01,940 --> 00:32:03,470
I can't afford to feed them.

693
00:32:04,010 --> 00:32:06,510
Regarding the issue of the female comrade staying or leaving,

694
00:32:06,510 --> 00:32:07,570
I think we should still respect

695
00:32:07,570 --> 00:32:09,030
Bai Ju's personal wishes.

696
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:11,220
I can't decide for her.

697
00:32:15,420 --> 00:32:15,940
Duojie.

698
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:20,420
About the guns and ammunition,

699
00:32:20,420 --> 00:32:21,140
I'll find a way

700
00:32:21,140 --> 00:32:22,270
to get you a bit more.

701
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:24,240
Shi is stingy.

702
00:32:24,330 --> 00:32:25,990
I'll keep pushing him for you.

703
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:26,790
Okay.

704
00:32:27,420 --> 00:32:28,160
On behalf of the boys,

705
00:32:28,160 --> 00:32:29,760
thank you, County Mayor Lin.

706
00:32:30,380 --> 00:32:31,160
Why are you running?

707
00:32:31,160 --> 00:32:32,310
I'm not asking you for a report.

708
00:32:32,310 --> 00:32:33,840
Why are you walking so fast?

709
00:32:34,510 --> 00:32:36,570
You're not rushing me for the report?

710
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:38,800
Then what do you want with me?

711
00:32:41,140 --> 00:32:42,240
It's about Bai Ju.

712
00:32:43,270 --> 00:32:44,270
Whether she stays or goes,

713
00:32:44,270 --> 00:32:45,930
or goes into the mountains...

714
00:32:46,090 --> 00:32:47,350
You are her direct supervisor,

715
00:32:47,350 --> 00:32:49,610
so you bear the primary responsibility.

716
00:32:49,610 --> 00:32:50,440
Anyway, in principle,

717
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:51,160
everything is to serve

718
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:52,270
the Mountain Patrol's mineral exploration.

719
00:32:52,270 --> 00:32:52,880
Lin.

720
00:32:54,250 --> 00:32:55,750
You know I hate meetings.

721
00:32:57,030 --> 00:32:58,180
I just finished one,

722
00:32:58,270 --> 00:32:59,930
and now you want a private one.

723
00:33:00,940 --> 00:33:02,540
Just say what you have to say.

724
00:33:05,480 --> 00:33:06,160
As for Bai Ju's background,

725
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:07,160
we all know it.

726
00:33:08,090 --> 00:33:09,000
I agree with her staying

727
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:10,330
in the Mountain Patrol.

728
00:33:10,530 --> 00:33:11,990
But my personal opinion is

729
00:33:12,880 --> 00:33:14,940
she shouldn't go into the mountains.

730
00:33:16,070 --> 00:33:17,870
Grass moves to attract the wind.

731
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:20,140
Flowers bloom to leave seeds.

732
00:33:21,200 --> 00:33:21,960
Can you control

733
00:33:21,960 --> 00:33:23,360
which way the wind blows?

734
00:33:23,980 --> 00:33:26,040
Then you're saying we should just...

735
00:33:31,110 --> 00:33:31,850
Anyway,

736
00:33:33,110 --> 00:33:35,170
as long as you've thought it through.

737
00:33:36,610 --> 00:33:37,680
Take this medicine.

738
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:37,920
Director.

739
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:39,010
Take it twice a day.

740
00:33:39,110 --> 00:33:39,700
Once in the morning and once at night.

741
00:33:39,700 --> 00:33:40,230
Ms. Kang.

742
00:33:40,510 --> 00:33:42,240
Take it 15 minutes after meals.

743
00:33:42,940 --> 00:33:43,570
Drink hot water.

744
00:33:43,570 --> 00:33:44,200
Don't drink unboiled water anymore.

745
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:44,600
Yanzi.

746
00:33:45,480 --> 00:33:46,030
Come home with me.

747
00:33:46,030 --> 00:33:47,560
Help me pick up some things.

748
00:33:48,110 --> 00:33:49,000
What things?

749
00:33:49,480 --> 00:33:50,540
Yangjin's two kids

750
00:33:50,640 --> 00:33:51,700
didn't bring enough clothes.

751
00:33:51,700 --> 00:33:53,030
I'll find some for them.

752
00:33:53,880 --> 00:33:54,380
Okay.

753
00:33:57,960 --> 00:33:58,350
Here.

754
00:34:00,770 --> 00:34:01,250
You kept

755
00:34:01,330 --> 00:34:02,390
all their clothes?

756
00:34:02,570 --> 00:34:04,500
These belong to Bai Chun and Bai Ji.

757
00:34:06,030 --> 00:34:06,980
There's another box,

758
00:34:06,980 --> 00:34:07,960
belonging to Bai Shao and her sister.

759
00:34:07,960 --> 00:34:08,920
Two years ago,

760
00:34:09,010 --> 00:34:10,070
I gave it away.

761
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:13,710
Isn't this too big?

762
00:34:13,800 --> 00:34:14,659
Yangjin's kids

763
00:34:14,730 --> 00:34:15,800
won't be able to wear it.

764
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:16,880
It doesn't matter.

765
00:34:17,130 --> 00:34:18,300
Let them take it back.

766
00:34:18,300 --> 00:34:19,280
Kids grow fast.

767
00:34:19,920 --> 00:34:20,590
Okay.

768
00:34:22,150 --> 00:34:22,679
This one.

769
00:34:23,530 --> 00:34:23,980
Here.

770
00:34:28,260 --> 00:34:28,860
Ma'am,

771
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:30,219
your skills are great.

772
00:34:30,710 --> 00:34:32,420
It's as good as a sewing machine.

773
00:34:32,420 --> 00:34:34,400
I practiced on the operating table.

774
00:34:34,400 --> 00:34:35,300
When a person's belly is cut open,

775
00:34:35,300 --> 00:34:36,650
I can sew it back up.

776
00:34:37,010 --> 00:34:38,340
Sewing this is nothing.

777
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:39,440
Okay.

778
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:40,960
And...

779
00:34:45,170 --> 00:34:46,690
This one is too worn out.

780
00:34:47,530 --> 00:34:48,570
Look at this.

781
00:34:48,670 --> 00:34:49,610
This is Bai Ji's.

782
00:34:50,070 --> 00:34:51,710
He was always fighting when he was little,

783
00:34:51,710 --> 00:34:53,300
but he could never win.

784
00:34:53,510 --> 00:34:54,710
He didn't dare ask me.

785
00:34:54,940 --> 00:34:56,030
So he always asked his brother

786
00:34:56,030 --> 00:34:57,090
to stand up for him.

787
00:34:58,670 --> 00:34:59,940
By the looks of it,

788
00:35:00,260 --> 00:35:01,130
he lost a lot.

789
00:35:01,570 --> 00:35:03,130
I tore some of them.

790
00:35:04,650 --> 00:35:05,050
You...

791
00:35:05,050 --> 00:35:06,850
No wonder he didn't dare ask you.

792
00:35:07,710 --> 00:35:09,260
You spanked him every time?

793
00:35:09,360 --> 00:35:10,610
It's from New Year's firecrackers.

794
00:35:10,610 --> 00:35:11,960
Burnt by the sparks.

795
00:35:12,260 --> 00:35:13,190
Look here.

796
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:14,690
It looks scorched.

797
00:35:16,670 --> 00:35:18,870
This one is too tattered. Let's toss it.

798
00:35:20,900 --> 00:35:21,690
When he was little,

799
00:35:21,690 --> 00:35:23,340
he was a little rascal.

800
00:35:23,440 --> 00:35:24,820
Now he's a big rascal.

801
00:35:25,300 --> 00:35:26,630
He's just adventurous.

802
00:35:29,480 --> 00:35:30,210
Give it to me.

803
00:35:52,260 --> 00:35:52,960
Is it heavy?

804
00:35:53,030 --> 00:35:53,550
Let me carry it.

805
00:35:53,550 --> 00:35:53,960
No need.

806
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:54,510
Let me.

807
00:37:16,900 --> 00:37:17,380
Get up.

808
00:37:17,980 --> 00:37:18,380
Get up.

809
00:37:18,380 --> 00:37:18,690
What's wrong?

810
00:37:18,690 --> 00:37:20,290
Look, this road isn't right.

811
00:37:22,780 --> 00:37:23,570
What's wrong with it?

812
00:37:23,570 --> 00:37:23,940
This road

813
00:37:23,940 --> 00:37:25,540
isn't going to Tianduo City.

814
00:37:25,980 --> 00:37:27,110
If we keep going,

815
00:37:27,530 --> 00:37:28,320
it'll take us straight into

816
00:37:28,320 --> 00:37:29,010
Bolamula.

817
00:37:29,440 --> 00:37:30,090
No way.

818
00:37:30,630 --> 00:37:31,360
Why do they want

819
00:37:31,360 --> 00:37:32,010
to take us there?

820
00:37:32,010 --> 00:37:32,320
In there,

821
00:37:32,320 --> 00:37:33,780
there isn't a single soul.

822
00:37:34,940 --> 00:37:36,320
Maybe they're taking a shortcut?

823
00:37:36,320 --> 00:37:37,380
Shortcut?

824
00:37:37,480 --> 00:37:38,510
I know this road.

825
00:37:38,900 --> 00:37:40,170
This goes to Bolamula.

826
00:37:40,940 --> 00:37:42,230
Something's wrong with this ride.

827
00:37:42,230 --> 00:37:44,030
Bolamula is a Uninhabited Zone.

828
00:37:44,210 --> 00:37:44,730
You sound like

829
00:37:44,730 --> 00:37:45,840
you've been there.

830
00:37:45,940 --> 00:37:46,380
I...

831
00:37:46,480 --> 00:37:47,030
I just...

832
00:37:48,380 --> 00:37:48,940
Bro,

833
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:51,100
do you really know this road?

834
00:37:51,880 --> 00:37:52,650
Really.

835
00:37:52,730 --> 00:37:55,530
This is definitely going to the Uninhabited Zone.

836
00:37:55,590 --> 00:37:56,090
Right.

837
00:37:56,920 --> 00:37:58,530
His sister is a police officer.

838
00:37:58,530 --> 00:38:00,130
She's in charge of Bolamula.

839
00:38:00,360 --> 00:38:02,020
He definitely knows the road.

840
00:38:02,230 --> 00:38:02,650
Right.

841
00:38:03,070 --> 00:38:04,130
My sister is a police officer.

842
00:38:04,130 --> 00:38:05,420
I've been here with her.

843
00:38:05,420 --> 00:38:05,960
If you don't believe me,

844
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:06,940
you should believe the police.

845
00:38:06,940 --> 00:38:07,780
What do we do now?

846
00:38:07,780 --> 00:38:08,730
What should we do?

847
00:38:08,730 --> 00:38:09,380
Now, we...

848
00:38:09,460 --> 00:38:10,070
Stop thinking!

849
00:38:10,070 --> 00:38:10,880
Run!

850
00:38:25,760 --> 00:38:26,630
What's that noise?

851
00:38:26,630 --> 00:38:28,290
What's happening back there?

852
00:38:29,550 --> 00:38:30,680
Someone jumped off!

853
00:38:35,980 --> 00:38:36,840
Stop!

854
00:38:43,420 --> 00:38:44,170
Stop!

855
00:38:47,590 --> 00:38:48,530
Nima!

856
00:38:49,570 --> 00:38:50,280
Bro!

857
00:38:50,530 --> 00:38:51,190
Don't move.

858
00:38:53,840 --> 00:38:54,420
Go back! Hurry!

859
00:38:54,420 --> 00:38:54,980
Bai Ji!

860
00:38:57,340 --> 00:38:58,000
Bai Ji!

861
00:38:58,500 --> 00:38:59,820
Run!

862
00:38:59,940 --> 00:39:01,110
Run!

863
00:39:01,530 --> 00:39:03,000
Run!

864
00:39:03,710 --> 00:39:04,300
Go back!

865
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:05,800
Run!

866
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:07,280
Run!

867
00:39:14,170 --> 00:39:14,780
Go to the pharmacy

868
00:39:14,780 --> 00:39:15,730
and prescribe some more painkillers

869
00:39:15,730 --> 00:39:16,280
and anti-inflammatories.

870
00:39:16,280 --> 00:39:16,610
Okay.

871
00:39:16,650 --> 00:39:17,210
And I'll go over there

872
00:39:17,210 --> 00:39:19,270
and check their temperatures again.

873
00:39:22,260 --> 00:39:22,920
Director Zhang!

874
00:39:22,920 --> 00:39:23,650
Nima!

875
00:39:23,760 --> 00:39:25,020
Who did you fight with?

876
00:39:25,610 --> 00:39:26,940
I'm looking for Director Zhang!

877
00:39:26,940 --> 00:39:27,860
Director Zhang is busy.

878
00:39:27,860 --> 00:39:28,420
Tell me first.

879
00:39:28,420 --> 00:39:29,210
Where are you hurt?

880
00:39:29,210 --> 00:39:29,960
It's not me.

881
00:39:30,940 --> 00:39:32,030
Bai Ji!

882
00:39:32,360 --> 00:39:33,090
Bai Ji?

883
00:39:33,190 --> 00:39:34,500
Bai Ji has been taken!

884
00:39:35,590 --> 00:39:36,920
What happened to Bai Ji?

885
00:39:37,360 --> 00:39:37,840
Didn't Bai Ji

886
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:39,340
just come out of the Uninhabited Zone?

887
00:39:39,340 --> 00:39:40,710
How did he get kidnapped by traffickers?

888
00:39:40,710 --> 00:39:42,510
He went to the Uninhabited Zone?

889
00:39:42,570 --> 00:39:43,340
Your brother was doing dirty work,

890
00:39:43,340 --> 00:39:44,600
and you didn't tell me?

891
00:39:45,510 --> 00:39:46,480
No, I planned to go back after work

892
00:39:46,480 --> 00:39:47,190
and tell you.

893
00:39:47,190 --> 00:39:48,380
Who knew he'd get in trouble again?

894
00:39:48,380 --> 00:39:49,260
Call the police, now.

895
00:39:49,260 --> 00:39:50,380
We must catch them!

896
00:40:45,210 --> 00:40:46,400
There's a car following us.

897
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:47,200
Drive faster.

898
00:40:58,480 --> 00:40:59,150
Ju!

899
00:40:59,670 --> 00:41:00,400
Ju!

900
00:41:00,480 --> 00:41:01,130
I'm over here!

901
00:41:01,130 --> 00:41:01,610
Police!

902
00:41:02,170 --> 00:41:02,960
Help!

903
00:41:04,090 --> 00:41:05,440
Help!

904
00:41:05,510 --> 00:41:06,010
Help!

905
00:41:45,280 --> 00:41:45,820
Police!

906
00:41:46,130 --> 00:41:46,920
Turn off the engine and get out of the car

907
00:41:46,920 --> 00:41:47,850
for inspection!

908
00:41:47,860 --> 00:41:48,400
Get out!

909
00:41:50,650 --> 00:41:51,480
She's police.

910
00:41:51,570 --> 00:41:52,570
She has a gun, too.

911
00:41:57,760 --> 00:41:58,380
Hurry up!

912
00:42:00,340 --> 00:42:01,340
And you!

913
00:42:01,460 --> 00:42:02,300
Come here now!

914
00:42:03,940 --> 00:42:04,470
Hurry up!

915
00:42:11,800 --> 00:42:12,530
Stand still!

916
00:42:14,550 --> 00:42:15,500
Officer,

917
00:42:15,610 --> 00:42:16,630
were we overloaded

918
00:42:16,630 --> 00:42:17,460
or speeding?

919
00:42:18,230 --> 00:42:18,780
Someone reported

920
00:42:18,780 --> 00:42:20,640
that you're trafficking people.

921
00:42:21,010 --> 00:42:22,470
It's a misunderstanding.

922
00:42:22,510 --> 00:42:24,130
We're from the cement factory.

923
00:42:24,130 --> 00:42:25,070
These are workers

924
00:42:25,070 --> 00:42:26,230
who ran away from the factory.

925
00:42:26,230 --> 00:42:27,710
They all signed contracts.

926
00:42:27,710 --> 00:42:29,570
We wouldn't do anything illegal.

927
00:42:33,630 --> 00:42:34,460
Squat down!

928
00:42:34,550 --> 00:42:35,110
Move!

929
00:42:35,590 --> 00:42:36,390
Go over there!

930
00:42:37,730 --> 00:42:38,360
Officer,

931
00:42:38,460 --> 00:42:39,010
help us!

932
00:42:39,610 --> 00:42:40,410
Stop yelling.

933
00:42:50,570 --> 00:42:51,030
Get up!

934
00:42:53,440 --> 00:42:54,240
Go over there!

935
00:43:01,380 --> 00:43:02,150
Officer,

936
00:43:06,230 --> 00:43:07,500
Come on, untie me, Ju!
